===Etymology===
See [[Aotearoa]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/aʊəteɪ'roʊən/}}, {{IPA|/'aɔtea'rɔan/}}
* {{SAMPA|/%aU@teI"roU@n/}}, {{SAMPA|/"aOtea"rOan/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#A person from [[Aotearoa]]/[[New Zealand]] ''(very rare)''.

====Quotation====
"If all New Zealanders were brought up understanding Maori... then, we would all be New Zealanders&mdash;or should that read Aotearoans?" (New Zealand Listener, 1993)

====Synonyms====
*[[New Zealander]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# From or pertaining to [[Aotearoa]]/[[New Zealand]] or to a person from there.

====Usage notes====
The adjective sense is very rare.

